Econometric Identification: IV-Probit and ARDL Bounds
The quantitative analysis will go beyond the descriptive statistics used in the Master's (SPSS frequency tables) to include:
1) Instrumental Variable Probit (IV-Probit): To solve the endogeneity of insurance uptake.
2) ARDL Bounds Testing: To examine the long-run equilibrium relationship between insurance coverage and agricultural productivity.
3) Lewbel approach: To disentangle ex-ante (investment) and ex-post (payout) impacts of index-based insurance.
Strategic Frameworks and Behavioural Nudges
Building on the Master’s recommendation for "smart subsidies," the PhD explores the "Institutionalization Framework" of the UNDP Insurance and Risk Finance Facility. It investigates the role of behavioural science, such as "trust messengers" and "premium rebates," which have been shown to increase willingness to participate by 20% in similar African contexts.
