Conclusion: Expanding the Thesis into a Policy Vision
The Master's thesis concluded that the Eastern Province was in a state of "uninsured vulnerability". This doctoral program expands that conclusion into an actionable policy vision, positioning inclusive insurance as the primary de-risking tool for Zambia’s industrialization. By tripling the sample size and employing robust causal models, this research aims to provide the evidentiary weight needed to integrate insurance into the core of Zambia's agricultural structural transformation.
